
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes to the result of a [data.read] operation. It retrieves the [limit] and [offset] nodes from the [.arguments] node using [get-nodes] and adds them to the result set. The [add] slot is used to combine the results of multiple node retrieval operations.
add:x:./*/data.read
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/limit
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/offset
